The presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the 2019 general elections, Atiku Abubakar, has dissociated himself from the posters littering the streets of Abuja
 
The Media Adviser to the former vice president in a statement in Abuja on Wednesday, declared: “our attention has been drawn to posters of His Excellency, Atiku Abubakar, Presidential candidate of Peoples Democratic Party in the 2019 elections, being circulated in Abuja bearing his identity.
“We disassociate the former Vice President of Nigeria from the said posters in circulation.”
The media adviser noted that the campaign season is over. ‘The tainted electoral victory by the incumbent is being challenged in court.
“We refuse to be distracted, which is exactly the objective of our opponents, but to remain focused on diligently pursuing our election petition with a view to retrieving the stolen mandate,” he declared.

			
